As he played his checkmate at the end, tarriff178 advised me to look at move 25:
"Look at move 25. You could have taken my Bishop with QxBc5".  I'm looking but it seems to me he just takes back with Qxc5.  What have I missed?  25. Qxe2 looks good though and was part of my original thinking, skewering the 2 Bs from e7.  One of the problems playing lots of games simultaneously on line is that I easily lose my train of thought, so probably just forgot what I'd planned and failed to spot the hanging B.  Note to self: study the board before moving!
